snippet: Top contenders in both nations failed to get enough votes on Sunday to win outright, in contests that tested the power of incumbent parties.
abstract: Presidential elections in El Salvador and Costa Rica will head to a second round after top contenders in both nations fail to get enough votes to win outright, in contests that test the power of incumbent parties.
lead_paragraph: Top contenders in both nations failed to get enough votes on Sunday to win outright, in contests that tested the power of incumbent parties.
